<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1089,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1952,1979]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Comments.</emphasis>
This is an unusual species within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[837,972,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,972,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Hoplothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The transversely striate sculpture on the head is a character state more commonly associated with species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[954,1057,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[954,1057,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage.
</paragraph>
